snippet: The House Committee on Energy and Commerce said Wednesday that only two-thirds of people signing up for private health insurance in the federal exchange had paid by April 15.
abstract: House Committee on Energy and Commerce says only two-thirds of people who signed up for private health insurance in federal exchange paid their premiums by April 15; without payment, consumers will not have coverage; Obama administration questions data, which Republican Rep Fred Upton, chairman of committee, says provides true picture of national enrollment in the exchange as of mid-April.
lead_paragraph: The House Committee on Energy and Commerce said Wednesday that only two-thirds of people signing up for private health insurance in the federal exchange had paid by April 15.
